{
  "page": "Snowylocks",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\">Snowylocks</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Asoiaf_snowylocks_by_sickdelusion_by_sickdelusion-d6wgdf3.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Asoiaf snowylocks by sickdelusion by sickdelusion-d6wgdf3.jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/30/Asoiaf_snowylocks_by_sickdelusion_by_sickdelusion-d6wgdf3.jpg/350px-Asoiaf_snowylocks_by_sickdelusion_by_sickdelusion-d6wgdf3.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"487\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/30/Asoiaf_snowylocks_by_sickdelusion_by_sickdelusion-d6wgdf3.jpg/525px-Asoiaf_snowylocks_by_sickdelusion_by_sickdelusion-d6wgdf3.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/30/Asoiaf_snowylocks_by_sickdelusion_by_sickdelusion-d6wgdf3.jpg/700px-Asoiaf_snowylocks_by_sickdelusion_by_sickdelusion-d6wgdf3.jpg 2x\" /></a><div>Snowylocks by SickDelusion ©</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Three-eyed_crow\" title=\"Three-eyed crow\">last greenseer</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Race</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Children_of_the_forest\" title=\"Children of the forest\">children of the forest</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i> (appears)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Snowylocks</b> is one of the <a href=\"/index.php/Children_of_the_forest\" title=\"Children of the forest\">children of the forest</a> in service to the <a href=\"/index.php/Three-eyed_crow\" title=\"Three-eyed crow\">last greenseer</a>. Her true name is too long for the human tongue, according to <a href=\"/index.php/Leaf\" title=\"Leaf\">Leaf</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance_and_Character\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance and Character</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance_and_Character\">Appearance and Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Snowylocks&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance and Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Snowylocks is white-haired.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Like the other children of the forest, she is smaller than humans, but not childlike. She has nut-brown skin, dappled like a <a href=\"/index.php/Deer\" title=\"Deer\">deer</a>'s with paler spots. Her hands have only three fingers and a thumb, with sharp black claws instead of nails. She has large ears that can hear things that no man can hear.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> She has large golden eyes slitted like those of a <a href=\"/index.php/Cat\" title=\"Cat\">cat</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> allowing her to see in dark passages.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>She does not speak the <a href=\"/index.php/Common_Tongue\" title=\"Common Tongue\">Common Tongue</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Snowylocks&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Snowylocks&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>In the <a href=\"/index.php/Cave_of_the_three-eyed_crow\" title=\"Cave of the three-eyed crow\">cave of the three-eyed crow</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Beyond_the_Wall\" title=\"Beyond the Wall\">beyond the Wall</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran Stark</a> and his companions <a href=\"/index.php/Meera_Reed\" title=\"Meera Reed\">Meera</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Jojen_Reed\" title=\"Jojen Reed\">Jojen Reed</a> meet a remnant of the children of the forest, who serve the <a href=\"/index.php/Last_greenseer\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Last greenseer\">last greenseer</a>, Lord Brynden. Their names are too long for the human tongue, according to <a href=\"/index.php/Leaf\" title=\"Leaf\">Leaf</a>, so Bran and Meera give them names. Meera names Snowylocks for the color of her hair. Bran does not know what Snowylocks thinks about her new name.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When Brynden says it is time for Bran to awaken his gifts as a <a href=\"/index.php/Greenseer\" title=\"Greenseer\">greenseer</a>, Leaf beckons, and Snowylocks brings forth a <a href=\"/index.php/Weirwood\" title=\"Weirwood\">weirwood</a> bowl carved with a dozen faces, like the ones the <a href=\"/index.php/Heart_tree\" title=\"Heart tree\">heart trees</a> wear. Inside the bowl is a white <a href=\"/index.php/Weirwood_seed_paste\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Weirwood seed paste\">weirwood seed paste</a>, thick and heavy, with dark red veins running through it. Snowylocks hands the bowl to Leaf to give to Bran to eat.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Snowylocks&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\">1.4</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\">1.5</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\">1.6</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_34\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 34\">Chapter 34</a>, Bran III.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_13\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 13\">Chapter 13</a>, Bran II.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403141606\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.073 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.245 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 795/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 1066